item.description:
what i learned you can use the tags raw and endraw to escape liquid tags.
how i learned in the previous TIL i tried to write the following
{% raw %} i am moving soyserg.io from a hugo site to jekyll and i couldn&rsquo;t figure out how to have nested {{}} as in {{ category/{{category | downcase }} | relative_url }} which just doesn&rsquo;t work. so i moved to {{ 'category/' | append: category | downcase | relative_url }} {% endraw %}
